 C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104sfb1665702805569.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/sfb1665702805569.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/sfb1665702805569.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"sfb1665702805569\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Define COM Properties (call-in)\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Define the call-in properties for COM implementations.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"sfb1665702805569__section_w53ab1b5b1_w54ab1b5_w55ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\"></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"sfb1665702805569__section_jck_ynf_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d480635e56\">Fields</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"sfb1665702805569__ul_ldp_ynf_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sfb1665702805569__li_d3143e1_d3144e1_d3145e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sfb1665702805569__p_d6440e1_d6441e1_d6442e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"tzb1665702753850.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tzb1665702753850.html\" title=\"Name of the COM ProgID.\">ProgID</a>\n</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sfb1665702805569__li_d3146e1_d3147e1_d3148e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sfb1665702805569__p_d6443e1_d6444e1_d6445e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xjr1665702753919.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xjr1665702753919.html\" title=\"Internal class ID of the COM component. It is automatically provided when the ProgID is selected.\">CLSID</a>\n</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"sfb1665702805569__section_fhx_znf_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d480635e92\">How to</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sfb1665702805569__p_d6380e1_d6381e1_d6382e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zzx1665702678830.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zzx1665702678830.html\" title=\"Use the Signature Editor to create or modify component signatures. Signatures of Uniface components are automatically generated during compilation. Signatures of non-Uniface components can be created or imported.\">Define a Component Signature</a>\n</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nwm1665702769167.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>COM and DCOM</a><p>To connect with COM components, Uniface makes use of the Microsoft's DCOM architecture. Uniface includes a COM connector that provides an interface with DCOM, thereby enabling Uniface components to call and be called by COM components.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_8422679\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_8422679\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Define COM Properties (call-in) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 20, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Define COM Properties (call-in) Define the call-in properties for COM implementations. Fields ProgID CLSID How to Define a Component Signature Related Links COM and DCOM To connect with COM components, Uniface makes use of the Microsoft's DCOM architecture. Uniface includes a COM connector that provides an interface with DCOM, thereby enabling Uniface components to call and be called by COM components. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}